      <acqinfo id="aspace_550c3d6c048f8726ad4a14eadc732594">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Files retained by the library after the publication of <title>
               <part>The Vinland Map and the Tartar Relation</part>
            </title> by Yale University Press.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_50f6dbd0d5d7292afb12fa5c488ce0f8">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_2adc2008fa8011c6ca53dfd2695c8972">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>The Vinland Map and the Tartar Relation: Proofs and Subject Files are the physical property of the Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library, Yale University. Copyright to the text of The Vinland Map and the Tartar Relation is held by Yale University. Literary rights, including copyright, to other material in the collection belong to the authors or their legal heirs and assigns.  For further information, consult the appropriate curator.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <processinfo id="aspace_58bf978b2aceba8e1fd2b249dfba43b7">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>This material received a basic level of processing, including minimal organization, in 2015.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_65d94b723f7c98cde35ff90d4a16c9df">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>
            <title>
               <part>The Vinland Map and the Tartar Relation</part>
            </title>: Proofs and Subject Files contains corrected and uncorrected proofs of this work on the "Vinland Map" (Beinecke MS 350A), as wells as extensive files of newspaper and magazine cliippings of book reviews, news items, and publicity about the map and the claims for its preColumbian origin.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_8f8ac69a5c9062698c1e008d3e943260">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into three groups: I. Proofs and proof sheets, 1964-1965; II. Subject Files, 1964-1966. III. Related Material, undated.</p>  
      </arrangement>
